          <p class="card-text">Indian tourism is a vibrant and diverse sector, reflecting the country's rich cultural heritage, historical landmarks, and natural beauty. Known as the land of unity in diversity, India offers a wide range of experiences, from ancient monuments like the Taj Mahal and Qutub Minar to serene backwaters in Kerala and breathtaking Himalayan landscapes. Visitors can explore bustling cities, tranquil beaches, lush forests, and spiritual destinations like Varanasi, Amritsar, and Rishikesh.</p>
          <p class="card-text">India's cuisine, festivals, art, and traditions add a unique charm to its tourism. With UNESCO World Heritage Sites, wildlife sanctuaries, hill stations, and adventure sports, the country caters to all types of travelers, making it a globally renowned travel destination.</p>
